column100: ,One day what happened to this old man and woman of ancient times? The old woman said to her husband, 'Dear, the way we are running our household, buying everything from the market, this is very difficult for us. So, it would be best to plant a vegetable garden and do some kind of gardening.' ",~~~,ML ID,"7apr2011, tpu",The Planting of Pán by the Old Man and Woman,n <NotSure> <NotSure>

column1: 5,mni,"‘ čummídá íbémmá mə́ču-taydə́ nə́ŋ ə́sé , ə́dúnidə́nə yúmbanbáydudi , ə́də́ iŋkholnedə́nə təwribsinə ə́təy yénšaŋ thabədi íphə́t-phə́tʔedo , mə́sídə phəgədəbəsidi pángə tharəbədi yamnə phənihé .’ ",
column76: ,The husband replied, 'My dear lady, you are absolutely right. You have much foresight and that's what makes this household run. Now, if we plant this garden you are talking about, it wouldn't be good if we planted just any vegetable. Regarding this, it would be best if we planted arum.' ",~~~,ML ID,"7apr2011, tpu",The Planting of Pán by the Old Man and Woman,punct

column28: ,"For this chutney it is our Meitei custom to use hénták or seasoned fish. [NOTE 28. Hénták is made by grinding together small dry fish, the stalk of arum and onions. These are then rolled into balls, sealed in airtight containers for at least two weeks, repounded and then used as flavoring bases for chutneys such as írónba. NOTE 29. As discussed in Chelliah (2000), the female nominalizer -pí grammaticalizes to form a part-whole marker.]",~~~,ML ID,"7apr2011, tpu",The Planting of Pán by the Old Man and Woman,n v>n <NotSure> <NotSure> <NotSure>

column25: ,In the olden days, hénták was popular, but ŋárí was not.",~~~,ML ID,"7apr2011, tpu",The Planting of Pán by the Old Man and Woman,<NotSure> Attachestoanycategory

column73: ,How was the hénták ‎‎seasoned? The bitter fish was first dried, then pounded with a cylinder into a fine powder pot. That is what is known as ŋárí. ",~~~,ML ID,"7apr2011, tpu",The Planting of Pán by the Old Man and Woman,n <NotSure>

column67: ,Then at last this sensible old man said, 'Hey, keep quiet! It will not be good if we do not beat the monkeys. They will surely come to ask how I am. I shall pretend to be ill, alright? When I pretend to be ill, you cry in the following way, ""You died by eating arum. Return to life by eating pumpkin!"" Then put me in a big earthen pot. After putting me in the pot, say, ""Your grandfather is dead so go and bury him."" They will carry the pot out with the intention of burying me, then I will jump out when they cross the narrow part of the gate, and I will beat those monkeys with a stick! I will finish off those monkeys right then and there.' ",~~~,ML ID,"7apr2011, tpu",The Planting of Pán by the Old Man and Woman,Attachestoanycategory <NotSure> <NotSure>

column1: 10,mni,"mə́mánə tə́n həwbə loyrə-mə́təm mə́tuŋ ə́sídə , kekrúhənǰəbəsinə mági kólhiŋ~kárə́bə , tháŋǰəw ə́mə ləy , háyribə tháŋǰəw ə́sí ləŋnə phéŋdətlə́gə , mə́réŋbándə thoŋgəttúnə , tə́n tə́rét ə́sí yómmə́gə , thə́bə́k súbə thórəkʔəmmí . ",mə́- má -=nə
column100: ,After his mother had finished cooking the flat breads, Lord of the Blackberry reached up to his shelf where there was a machete. Then, polishing that machete and hoisting it on his shoulder, he set out to find work with the seven flat breads he had wrapped.",~~~,ML ID,No comment,He Was Called Lord of the Blackberry,Attachestoanycategory <NotSure> <NotSure>

column40: ,Lord of the Blackberry had never worked since he was born, and so he did not even know where to go for work so he roamed around aimlessly.",~~~,ML ID,No comment,He Was Called Lord of the Blackberry,Attachestoanycategory <NotSure> Attachestoanycategory <NotSure>

column19: ,At last he grew tired after walking around so much.,~~~,ML ID,No comment,He Was Called Lord of the Blackberry,<NotSure> <NotSure> <NotSure>

column1: 13,mni,"wárəkpədəgi mə́háknə uməŋ ə́mədə čə́ŋsillə́gə , púkhrí ə́məgi mə́pándə hə́wrəmbə íkóy-kóynə hə́wbə khoŋnaŋ pámbí ə́məgi mə́thə́ktə toŋdúnə , pótharəmmí . ",wá -rək -pə -=dəgi
column61: ,Being tired, he entered a forest and climbed up to rest on one of the pipal trees that was growing around the bank of a pond.",~~~,ML ID,No comment,He Was Called Lord of the Blackberry,<NotSure> v>v v>n <NotSure>

column1: 14,mni,"mə́təmsidə mánə wádə́nə , mə́réŋbándə tháŋǰəw ə́sí thoŋgətlə́gə , khoŋnaŋ mə́thə́k ə́sídə póthadúnə ləyriŋəydə , púkhrí ə́sídi íčəm-čəmbə púkhrí woyrəmdəbənina , laygi khóygi mə́čášiŋ hélóy tə́rétki sannəphəm íruǰəphəm oybə púkhríni . ",mə́- təm -=si -=də
column94: ,At that time, he had hoisted his machete upon his shoulder and was resting on top of the pipal tree. Now the pond was not an ordinary pond. column154: ,The nymphs told Lord of the Blackberry how the ring worked: ‘When you cast this ring, you need to smear some incense on the ground, venerate the ring and bend your mind carefully towards what you desire. column208: ,After climbing out, they said, ‘What are you doing? The other day you said you were not going to do anything to us, but having said that, now you’re again saying, ""I’m going to eat them up today."" When they asked him this, Lord of the Blackberry said, ‘Why did you all lie to me about the ring the other day? In your presence when you said, ""Produce!"" it produced all you asked for. Then when I cast it at my house, nothing was produced. I was extremely embarrassed in front of my mother. Now, because all of you have lied to me, I am going to kill you today.’",~~~,ML ID,No comment,He Was Called Lord of the Blackberry,Attachestoanycategory <NotSure> Attachestoanycategory

column361: ,‘Then the spirits, because they knew they were not ordinary beings, knew that something must have happened, so they asked the the Lord of the Blackberry, ‘Did you go directly to your house while carrying the ring or did you stop on the way to rest?’ When they asked him this, Lord of the Blackberry remembered and said, ‘Hmm, well, that day when I was rushing home, the darkness crept up on me and I was not able to reach home. I remembered that a friend of mine lived on the way and I went to his house and rested there that night.’ When he spoke thus, the nymphs understood what had happened and said, ‘O.K. right. If that is so, it seems that your friend has surely taken the ring. Then in place of that, he gave you an ordinary ring. So, don’t be angry today. We’ll give you a weapon that will allow you to stand up to your friend. Take these, give your friend a good beating and then question him.’ And so saying the nymphs gave Lord of the Blackberry a magical coil of rope and a hammer made from tamarind tree wood.",~~~,ML ID,No comment,He Was Called Lord of the Blackberry,Attachestoanycategory <NotSure>

column244: ,They, that is the nymphs said, ‘Tell rope-that-can-become-lasso to bind any person you want bound. When you do that, rope-that-can-become-lasso will bind the person you want bound. Say to the tamarind hammer-that-can-beat, ""Beat him,"" and just when you say that it will start beating him. Then, once you proceed in this way, after you beat your friend and then question him, he will certainly reveal all.’ Because of what they said, Lord of the Blackberry was once again happy and returned carrying the rope-that-can-become-lasso and tamarind hammer-that-can-beat.",~~~,ML ID,No comment,He Was Called Lord of the Blackberry,Attachestoanycategory <NotSure> <NotSure> <NotSure>

column226: ,Then, when he was torturing them thus, he said, ‘Friend, have you or have you not taken my ring?’ And at the time when he questioned them thus, his friend became humble: ‘Friend, the other evening when you told me not to look at your ring. I really wanted to see it, and then when I saw it, because it was so beautiful, I took it. Then I wrapped up an ordinary ring and put it in its place.’ Then Lord of the Blackberry said, ‘If that is so, if you don’t give it back to me right away, I will beat you to death.’",~~~,ML ID,No comment,He Was Called Lord of the Blackberry,Attachestoanycategory <NotSure> <NotSure>

column190: ,When he had returned, he said to his mother...When his mother saw him returning, she was seething with anger. She said, ‘The sluggard has returned again and for sure he is going to ask for flat bread to be made for him.’ Then he said, ‘Mother, don’t be angry today. The ring I brought yesterday was not the right one. I’ve brought the true ring today. Now, whenever we say, ""Produce!"" it will produce what we desire. So, from today onwards, we will be happy.’ When he said this to his mother, she did not believe him because he had been wrong about it the other day.",~~~,ML ID,No comment,He Was Called Lord of the Blackberry,Attachestoanycategory <NotSure> Attachestoanycategory

column361: ,The mother entered the palace and said that she had come to ask the king and the nobles for the beautiful princess for her son by saying, ‘Please, give her to me.’ Upon hearing this, all the nobility laughed, thinking at first that it was a joke. But then, when she said that she was in earnest, they became angry and said, ‘You have come here to request the king’s daughter from us for your son who has nothing, who is the son of a widow, who has no ambition to work, who resembles a blackberry, who is as dark as ink, who has an ugly face? That is an insult to us! Push that mother by the neck and drag her around!’ Then, the nobles harassed and pushed the mother around. She fell down and got up again and, once again being pushed, she struck the floor. Thus, with her gums bleeding, she was escorted out to her gate.",~~~,ML ID,No comment,He Was Called Lord of the Blackberry,Attachestoanycategory <NotSure> <NotSure>

column175: ,‘I can’t spend all this money my friend gave me,’ he thought. So he took out a small part of the entire sum, just three or four rupees and said to his wife, ‘Hey you, go!  Don’t take much money. Take this five rupee note. With these five rupees you should buy a fish. Also, paying the small amount of twenty-five paisa, buy the kind of fishing basket that is used with a fishing net and fishing trap.’ And saying this, he sent her off on the errand.",~~~,ML ID,No comment,The Two Friends,Attachestoanycategory <NotSure> <NotSure>

column268: ,Her husband said, ‘I have invited my friend for a meal tomorrow, and so he will surely come. Therefore, arrange a variety of dishes thus. After cleaning a big fish, you must put it inside the fishing basket. For now, keep it covered inside the pot. Tomorrow when my friend comes, what I will say is, ""Dear one, what are all the things you have made for us?"" You should reply thus, ""The market was so far out of my way that I wasn’t able to buy any fish yesterday."" Then I will pretend to be very angry with you. When I’m pretending to be angry, I will say, ""Bring me our cat that looks like a soybean and the angler’s fishing basket."" After that, you just please keep quiet.’",~~~,ML ID,No comment,The Two Friends,Attachestoanycategory <NotSure>

column217: ,While this was going on, what was the poor wise man doing? He was saying, ‘You know what? In the near future, once the cat has died, my friend will come and say to me, ""Pay me back."" Understand? Now, for the next deed, let’s do this. You go and get a small covered clothes basket. Put some fruit and condiments, some things to eat and drink, some cigarettes, and some intoxicating things in there. Got it?’ And when he had said that, after some edibles had been bought and placed in the small covered clothes basket, they stood the basket in the front utility outbuilding, near where the sugarcane grew.",~~~,ML ID,No comment,The Two Friends,<NotSure> Attachestoanycategory

column1: 81,mni,"mági phisabəgi nát utoŋ háybə utoŋ ə́dúmə , mə́taŋ namə kháŋbə , mə́taŋ namə kə́kthətpə , mə́rídu kábrəŋ mə́rínə pallə́gə séttə́nə , mə́də sunu yayŋə́ŋ tə́ydə́nə , mə́raŋ-mə́raŋ həllə́gə , lá-látón ə́mə sémme háyrə́gə , mə́dúnə mági sə́námə́hí kačində puǰa təwdə́nə thəmme , háyriŋəyŋəydə , noŋŋalləkpədə mági mə́rúpse čə́béŋ-čə́béŋ ŋáŋlakʔí , ‘ hə́wdóŋbí ə́mə yonsəllegə , ə́yŋóndəgi lupá čə́ní lə́wbə , ə́ybu ə́pə́ŋbə ǰhútmút təwbə , nə́ŋ kərigino mə́rúp , ə́y lupá čə́ní píyu .’ ",má -=ki
column226: ,He took the bamboo that was used in his wife’s weaving work, called nát bamboo, which had one end open and one end closed. He decorated it with silk, then smeared it with turmeric and lime. Then, after making it very colorful, he brought it to the alcove where the male deity of the house resided. Making a doily with the top of a banana leaf, he placed the pipe on the doily as if someone were about to perform a ceremony worshipping the pipe. After he did this, the next day, his friend came to him fuming, ‘You made up that story about the cat. You took two hundred rupees from me. You made a fool out of me with your dishonest deal. What kind of friend are you? Give me my two hundred rupees!’",~~~,ML ID,No comment,The Two Friends,<NotSure> <NotSure>

column163: ,So right then while she was still away at the market, the aforementioned man whirled that cylinder and it whizzed urururu. That woman was just returning from a visit to her father’s house when the cylinder hit her on her thigh, whizzed around her and fell. column346: ,The man throwing the cylinder, the Rich One, was preparing to throw the cylinder in front of the cabinet by balancing it on his index finger. He said, ‘About my throwing it in front of the court, it would not be suitable if your servant threw this in your midst. So, I’ll go behind you a little bit, out near the flower garden, and throw it there.’ Then, when he said this, the ministers all said, ‘OK throw it there, throw it there.’ Then, coming to the flower garden, holding the cylinder, he made it whirl uuuu uuuu uuuu uuuu. Now the king’s favorite queen, Pataysori, the newest queen, the one that had come after number ten, the eleventh one, the one the king had not been married to very long, had heard that a woman was to be produced from a cylinder. Since she did not believe this and she wanted to check it out, she said to the servants that she needed to use the outhouse very badly. But the ministers absolutely prevented her from going outside. They said, ‘Dear Lady, it is not possible for you to go outside. The royal decree is, ""Prohibit women from going anywhere outside."" ’",~~~,ML ID,No comment,The Two Friends,<NotSure> <NotSure> <NotSure> <NotSure>

column253: ,Oh hell! Our teachers were so unassuming. They were really modest. Not at all like, I don’t know how to put it, our teachers back home. Now, about how those teachers travel--it’s unbelievable! They go by foot, each carrying those big bags. Now, in Manipur, all the college lecturers just go by car, right? But over there, there is a custom of walking and that’s what they do. Now from our hostel, of the four who were my companions, two of us were there. It was Rita and myself. Then, what should I say, the teachers too were very nice. When we did not know stuff, when there was anything people didn’t know, they would say, ‘Just come and ask us.’ Now we have a physics teacher called R. Tagore who is a Bengali. He did a lot for us, Rita and me.",~~~,ML ID,No comment,Where Did You Go to School?,<NotSure> <NotSure> <NotSure>
